YTT200hr Graduates ✨

Stop listening to that same old story in your head because you just never know who’s waiting for you on the other side with open arms ready to support, encourage, and uplift you. Thank you so much to each and everyone of you for calling me into this container. I can’t wait to see what’s next for us all.

We are lights, we are healers, we are space holders, and we are one. 🫶🏻💚✨

Let’s talk about journaling. In 2021 I was going through a difficult time with my body which took a big toll on my mind. My good friend/supporter @_niclap suggested journaling. Journaling was the last thing I wanted to do because it just made me more symptomatic but I gave it a try.

I truly believe I’m graduating tomorrow from YTT200HR because I journaled about it so many times. I’m not one to go out of my comfort zone especially when it comes to a “classroom” environment. I knew yoga and meditation was crucial to my healing and I can’t wait to share the gift.✨

Thank you, thank you, thank you. 

There are no words just an amazing experience with the best group of souls.
We did it.
💚✨🌱🫶🏻

I’m so excited to be creating a safe space for your own healing journey.

January 2021 I bumped my head for the third time in the same spot. An MRI showed possible brain damage from a car accident in 2012. 
Shortly after this I started to experience autonomic dysfunction (POTs). Anyone who has experienced #POTs hands on knows it’s no fun for anyone involved. Most days are spent resting in bed wishing you had the energy and body to do more.
The neuro threw a script at me and told me to go do all these tests which personally just stressed me out more. Stress is disease causing. If stress is not relieved damage happens in our bodies. Having such a sensitive body I knew this, I felt this daily. 
I started searching holistic options for #migraines and POTs/TBI.  These options helped more than the script that made me emotionless. 
Then I started practicing yoga for my issues and the rest was history…

Let’s heal together, join me on your mat Monday’s at 10:30am. PM class to be announced soon. ☺️🫶🏻✨

Treated myself to lunch on the beach with a dear friend. Then went in for a ocean cleanse after work today. 🌊✨🫶🏻

Only love can set you free. Yesterday was filled with so much love.

I started the afternoon with wellness Wednesday at @saltspastuart. A relaxing and peaceful environment to melt the stress and tension away. Then I headed over to @psychicnthegenie2 to visit my soul sister. What an amazing spot. My timing aligned perfectly. @kayleekinkela arrived right after me for oracle readings. Something I’ve been itching to try! The reading left me speechless. My jaw dropped, and my eyes watered. Everything she said was so true and aligned with what I was going through. It was what I needed to hear to confirm, I’m on my right path.

First leg day (brain day) of the year!
2023 had some loses I never expected. Another year filled with growth. 
Naturally, I ended the year in the ER after a dog bite. Dogs have always been my passion and career choice. This year I feel called to focus more on my healing journey while creating a save container for others to do the same. I can’t wait for you to practice with me!
The 2024 word I chose for myself and others is: trust.

You are exactly where you need to be. 💚✨🫶🏻
